{
  "version": 2,
  "builds": [
    { "src": "api/ai.js", "use": "@vercel/node" }
  ],
  "routes": [
    { "src": "/api/(.*)", "dest": "/api/$1" },
    { "src": "/(.*)", "dest": "/dsahub.html" }
  ]
}
```

The problems with the old one:
- Missing `"version": 2` — Vercel requires this
- `"rewrites"` is not valid in all Vercel plan types — `"routes"` is more compatible
- Missing `"builds"` to tell Vercel how to handle your Node.js serverless function

**Steps:**
1. Replace your `vercel.json` with the above
2. Make sure your folder structure looks like this:
```
your-project/
├── api/
│   └── ai.js
├── dsahub.html
├── style.css
├── script.js
├── package.json
└── vercel.json